  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Level Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- International information sharing\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance:\n- Financial institutions must implement strict verification processes\n- Regular audits and reporting\n- Training employees on detection methods\n\n5. Technological Solutions:\n- Advanced digital tracking systems\n- Artificial intelligence for pattern recognition\n- Blockchain technology for transparent transactions\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes by establishing comprehensive regulatory mechanisms across different jurisdictions.",
